<task id="AIPU-032" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Chat history panel component (session list, search, resume)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <wave>3</wave>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, shared-library, chat-history</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>003</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the chat history panel component for the @spaarke/ai-outputs library. The chat history panel lives in the left pane of the three-pane layout (or as a slide-out drawer) and lets users browse previous chat sessions, search session titles/summaries, and resume a prior conversation.

    The component is purely presentational with respect to data — it receives session data via props (no BFF API calls inside the component). The calling code page uses useChatSession from @spaarke/ai-context to fetch sessions and passes them down as props.

    Deliverables (all in src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/):
    1. ChatHistoryPanel.tsx — the main panel component with session list, search field, and empty state.
    2. ChatSessionCard.tsx — a single session card showing title, last message preview, timestamp, and entity context badge.
    3. useChatHistoryFilter.ts — a local hook that takes sessions[] and a search string, returns filtered sessions (client-side, no debounce required beyond a 200ms debounce).
    4. ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts — TypeScript type definitions for the panel (ChatSession, ChatHistoryPanelProps, ChatSessionCardProps).
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in React 19, Fluent UI v9, and shared component library authoring</role>

  <goal>
    A complete chat history panel (ChatHistoryPanel, ChatSessionCard, useChatHistoryFilter, types) exported from @spaarke/ai-outputs, displaying sessions with search filtering and resume callback, with full dark mode support and TypeScript compilation passing.
  </goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatHistoryPanel.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatSessionCard.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/useChatHistoryFilter.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/package.json</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/useChatSession.ts</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All components must use Fluent v9 makeStyles with design tokens only. No hard-coded hex colors, no inline style color values. Dark mode must work via FluentProvider theme switching.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Every public component, hook, and type must be exported from src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NOT PCF-safe. May use React 19 features (useTransition for search filtering, etc.) freely.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No BFF API calls inside ChatHistoryPanel or ChatSessionCard. The component receives sessions as a prop. The calling code page is responsible for data fetching via useChatSession from @spaarke/ai-context.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">@spaarke/ai-outputs must NOT take a package dependency on @spaarke/ai-context (to avoid circular deps). The ChatSession type is defined locally in ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts. If useChatSession returns the same shape, that is coincidental — no import from ai-context.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">useChatHistoryFilter debounce: 200ms debounce on the search string using a useEffect + setTimeout pattern (no lodash.debounce or external debounce library).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ChatHistoryPanel must show an empty state (Fluent v9 EmptyState pattern or equivalent: illustration area + title text + subtitle text) when sessions[] is empty or all sessions are filtered out by search.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ChatSessionCard "Resume" button calls an onResume?: (sessionId: string) =&gt; void prop. Button hidden if onResume not provided.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ChatSessionCard entity context badge: shows entityType and entityName (e.g., "Matter — Acme Corp v Smith"). Uses Fluent v9 Badge component in informative appearance.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
