      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/ai-assistant-theming.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 search input" location="@fluentui/react-components">
        Use SearchBox from @fluentui/react-components (v9) for the session search field. If SearchBox is not available in the installed version, use Input with search icon via contentBefore.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Card for session items" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/">
        Use Card, CardHeader, CardPreview from @fluentui/react-components for ChatSessionCard. Refer to any existing Card usage in shared components.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="useChatSession hook shape" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/useChatSession.ts">
        Read this file to understand the ChatSession data shape returned by the hook, then mirror the relevant fields in ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts ChatSession interface. Do not import from ai-context — just match the shape.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 makeStyles" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PanelSplitter/PanelSplitter.tsx">
        Reference for correct makeStyles import and token usage pattern.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/useChatSession.ts to understand the ChatSession data shape (fields: id, title, lastMessagePreview, updatedAt, entityType, entityName, entityId, etc.). Note the shape — do not import from this file.</step>
    <step>Read src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts to understand current exports and how to append new exports.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts:
      - ChatSession interface: { id: string; title: string; lastMessagePreview?: string; updatedAt: string; entityType?: string; entityName?: string; entityId?: string }
      - ChatHistoryPanelProps: { sessions: ChatSession[]; isLoading?: boolean; onResume?: (sessionId: string) =&gt; void; onDelete?: (sessionId: string) =&gt; void; className?: string }
      - ChatSessionCardProps: { session: ChatSession; onResume?: (sessionId: string) =&gt; void; onDelete?: (sessionId: string) =&gt; void; isActive?: boolean }
      Export all types.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/useChatHistoryFilter.ts:
      - Signature: useChatHistoryFilter(sessions: ChatSession[], searchQuery: string): ChatSession[]
      - Implements 200ms debounce on searchQuery using useEffect + setTimeout + clearTimeout cleanup
      - Filters on title and lastMessagePreview (case-insensitive substring match)
      - Returns all sessions if debounced query is empty
      Export useChatHistoryFilter.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatSessionCard.tsx:
      - Props: ChatSessionCardProps
      - Render a Fluent v9 Card with:
        - Title (Text semibold, truncated to 1 line)
        - lastMessagePreview (Text, truncated to 2 lines, muted color token)
        - updatedAt formatted as relative time (e.g., "2 hours ago") using Intl.RelativeTimeFormat
        - Entity badge: Badge informative with "{entityType} — {entityName}" if entityType present
        - "Resume" Button (primary appearance) — visible only if onResume prop provided
        - "Delete" Button (subtle appearance, danger icon) — visible only if onDelete prop provided
      - Use makeStyles.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatHistoryPanel.tsx:
      - Props: ChatHistoryPanelProps
      - Top section: SearchBox (or Input) for search query, bound to local useState
      - Use useChatHistoryFilter(sessions, searchQuery) for filtered list
      - If isLoading: render Fluent v9 Spinner centered
      - If filteredSessions.length === 0 and not loading: render empty state (Fluent v9 Body1 centered: "No conversations found" with appropriate icon)
      - Otherwise: render a scrollable list of ChatSessionCard components
      - Use makeStyles for layout (flexbox column, overflow-y auto).</step>
    <step>Update src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts to export: ChatHistoryPanel, ChatSessionCard, useChatHistoryFilter, and all types from ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts (ChatSession, ChatHistoryPanelProps, ChatSessionCardProps).</step>
    <step>Run TypeScript compilation check: cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs &amp;&amp; npx tsc --noEmit to confirm zero errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts defines ChatSession, ChatHistoryPanelProps, and ChatSessionCardProps interfaces with correct field types — all exported. No import from @spaarke/ai-context.</criterion>
    <criterion>useChatHistoryFilter applies a 200ms debounce to the search query and filters sessions by title and lastMessagePreview (case-insensitive). Returns all sessions when query is empty.</criterion>
    <criterion>ChatSessionCard renders session title (1-line truncation), lastMessagePreview (2-line truncation), relative updatedAt timestamp, entity context Badge (when entityType present), and conditional Resume/Delete buttons.</criterion>
    <criterion>ChatHistoryPanel renders a SearchBox at the top, a Spinner when isLoading is true, an empty state message when filteredSessions is empty, and a scrollable ChatSessionCard list otherwise.</criterion>
    <criterion>Empty state is shown both when sessions[] is initially empty and when all sessions are filtered out by search.</criterion>
    <criterion>All components use makeStyles with Fluent v9 design tokens only — no hard-coded hex colors or inline style color values.</criterion>
    <criterion>ChatHistoryPanel, ChatSessionCard, useChatHistoryFilter, and all types from ChatHistoryPanel.types.ts are exported from src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts.</criterion>
    <criterion>@spaarke/ai-outputs package.json does not list @spaarke/ai-context as a dependency or peerDependency.</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compilation passes with zero errors (npx tsc --noEmit).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
